ACCIDENTAL RELEASE PREVENTION AND EMERGENCY RESPONSE POLICIES: 
Aerosols Danville Inc. DBA Voyant Beauty is committed to promoting a safe operating environment for the facility, its employees and the surrounding community. The facility is complying with OSHA's Process Safety Management (PSM) standard, and EPA's Risk Management Program rule. The purpose of these regulations is to ensure that the covered process (aerosol packaging) is designed, operated and maintained safely. Compliance with these regulations helps to prevent releases from this process. Additionally, these regulations require development of procedures to minimize releases if they do occur, and to outline appropriate emergency response steps to take in the event of a release.

FACILITY DESCRIPTION AND REGULATED SUBSTANCES: 
Aerosols Danville Inc. DBA Voyant Beauty owns and operates a facility in Danville, Illinois and offers full service custom packaging for various consumer product industries, such as pharmaceutical, household, cosmetic, and personal care. The products packaged for these industries consist of liquids, semi-liquid creams, lotions, and aerosols. Some of the types of products that Aerosols Danville Inc. DBA Voyant Beauty packages include: hair products, body sprays, shaving creams, household cleaners, etc. Many of these products are aerosols and use a flammable gas like propane to pressurize the containers so that the desired product can be sprayed from the aerosol cans. The regulated chemicals used as propellants in the aerosol packaging process are:

Butane (CAS No. 106-97-8);
Difluoroethane (CAS No. 75-37-6):
Dimethylether (Methyl ether) (CAS No. 115-10-6);
Isobutane (CAS No. 75-28-5);
Propane (CAS No. 74-98-6);
Isopentane (CAS No. 78-78-4).

Process equipment includes propellant storage tanks, a tank farm for ingredients, filling, packaging, and warehouse equipment. 

